<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910503-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>910503-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Arnold Industries Inc.:   First-Period Net Rose 10%;   Dividend Raised, Stock Split</HL><DATE>05/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C16</SO><CO>   AIND</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>DIVIDENDS (DIV)EARNINGS (ERN)COMMERCIAL TRUCKING AND RELATED WAREHOUSING (TRK)</IN><NS>DIVIDENDS (DIV)EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>PENNSYLVANIA (PA)</RE><LP>   Arnold Industries Inc. reported record first-quarterearnings, boosted its quarterly dividend 20% and announced a2-for-1 stock split.   Arnold, which has interests in trucking, assembling,distribution and warehousing, reported a 10% gain infirst-quarter net income to $5.4 million, or 42 cents ashare, from $4.9 million, or 38 cents a share, a yearearlier. Revenue increased 2.5% to $39.5 million from $38.5million. First-quarter 1990 results were adjusted to reflectthe stock split.</LP><TEXT>   The Lebanon, Pa., company also said it will pay a dividendof 15 cents a share payable June 1 to stockholders of recordMay 16. Before the stock split, per-share dividends were 25cents.   The stock split will be distributed on June 21 tostockholders of record May 16, Arnold said.</TEXT></DOC>